{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":44611,"name":"Brian Knox","username":"najak3d","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-02-05T04:59:31.455Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThis is for very crude shadows, to improve on our current rendering of low-poly objects, onto a terrain not setup for shadows.   What we have is “good” for our app/context, but simply want to add the blob to help make the objects set on the ground look a little more realistic.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHere’s a screenshot of our Urho App, showing 2 Tower icons sitting on the green terrain.   And so we want to add circular blobs around the base of each tower.   We’ll have up to 2000 towers in the scene at once.    As far as blob shadows, we could just apply those to the towers close by, which will only be around 100 towers in close range max, at a time.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSo we could have a pool of 100 blob shadows that get swapped to the closest 100 towers, and that would suffice.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eQuestions:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIs Decals the best easy way to do this?  Or should be consider another technique?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCan Decals be Pooled and re-positioned easily/efficiently?  Or is it better to destroy and re-create them?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/2/22e3dc1892512375cae09bf84fd92071a1ae27d8.png\" data-download-href=\"/uploads/short-url/4YEq7jzMemEHpPRDIMHM3zSEn44.png?dl=1\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/2/22e3dc1892512375cae09bf84fd92071a1ae27d8_2_466x500.png\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"4YEq7jzMemEHpPRDIMHM3zSEn44\" width=\"466\" height=\"50